	"system": {
		"description": {
			"value": "<p><em>You slam a small block of granite into the ground, and as you do so, a large wall of granite rises up into the air.</em></p><p><strong>Summoning Spell</strong></p><p>You create a wall of stone.</p><ul><li><p>The wall is to immune to &amp;reference[poison]{poison} and &amp;reference[psychic]{psychic} damage, resistant to &amp;reference[cold]{cold}, &amp;reference[fire]{fire}, &amp;reference[lightning]{electric}, &amp;reference[radiant]{radiant}, &amp;reference[necrotic]{necrotic}, as well as &amp;reference[adamantine]{non-adamantine} &amp;reference[bludgeoning]{bludgeoning}, &amp;reference[piercing]{piercing}, and &amp;reference[slashing]{slashing} damage. It is also immune to all conditions except cover and &amp;reference[obscured]{obscured}.</p></li><li><p>It has AC 15, 30* hit points, and all its ability scores are 0, except &amp;reference[constitution]{constitution} which is 16.</p></li><li><p><span>If a creature occupies part of the area where you summon the wall, they roll a save:</span></p></li></ul><p><span> <strong>[[/save dex]]{Dexterity Save}</strong></span></p><ul><li><p><strong>Failure:</strong> <span>You move the creature to one side of the wall of your choice.</span></p></li><li><strong>Success:</strong> The creature moves to the nearest unoccupied space of their choice.</li></ul><p><strong>*Upcasting:</strong> For each spell level above 5th level, it gains 10 more hit points.</p>",
			"chat": ""
		},
